Exemplified compounds were found to have a pEC50>6.0.
Ki=EC50(1+([L]/KD)) 
Where EC50=Concentration at point of inflection, [L]=radioligand concentration and KD=equilibrium dissociation constant for the radioligand (expressed in the appropriate units of concentration).
Non-linear regression and one site binding (hyperbola) used for calculation of ligand concentration, KD (nM) and Bmax (pmol/mg protein) values:
Clozapine used as a reference; total binding determined by 1% DMSO; and non-specific binding determined by 10 μM clozapine.
